Whisperwind Error Handling Consideration (will add more if I think more)

1. Validation Input
Empty Commands - to ensure code is not preocessing when user accidently press enter
Whitespace - reject tasks with empty description
Null checks - prevents null exception

2. Number & Index Safety
Invalid numbers: catched non numeric inputs
out of bounds: prevent handling non existance task
negative/zero: ensure task start number from 1

3. Data Integrity
Empty Description: to ensure the data have meaningful content
Missing Component: validates all parts of deadlines/events exist
Duplication operations: prevent not neccessary mark/unmark operation

Specific Error Checks:

Command Level
Empty input → "Say something!"
Invalid command → "I don't know that command!"
Missing parameters → "Which task are we marking?"

Task Creation
Empty todo → "What's the todo?"
Invalid deadline format → "Use: deadline DESCRIPTION /by TIME"
Missing event times → "Need both start and end times"
Whitespace-only inputs → "Give me the details!"

Task Operations
Invalid task numbers → "That number doesn't exist!"
Already marked/unmarked → "Task is already done/undone!"
Empty task list → "Your list is empty!"



